byline.original: By G.H. ARCHAMBAULT Wireless to THE NEW YORK TIMES

abstract: German planes attempt to reach Paris
snippet: PARIS, Jan. 2--With the cold becoming keener and much snow still under foot, activity on the Western Front is best described as relative--very real to the men who must continue to patrol, but virtually insignificant from a military point of view....

headline.main: WEATHER CURTAILS WEST FRONT ACTION; Cold and Snow Under Foot Hold Fighting to Clashes of Scattered Patrols

lead_paragraph: PARIS, Jan. 2--With the cold becoming keener and much snow still under foot, activity on the Western Front is best described as relative--very real to the men who must continue to patrol, but virtually insignificant from a military point of view.
